column1: OMAP-21: Organ Mapping Antibody Panel (OMAP) for Multiplexed Antibody-Based Imaging of Palatine Tonsil (FFPE) with MACSima

column2: Werner Müller; Julia Femel; Silvia Rüberg; Andreas Bosio
Andrea J. Radtke; Ellen M. Quardokus

column24: rationale

BCL2 represents an anti-apoptotic protein highly expressed in mantle zone B cells and follicular lymphoma tumor B cells. This marker can be used to define the mantle zone (high expression) and germinal center (negative) in the tonsil. This marker is not a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
CD279 (PD1) is expressed on activated T and B cells (also on T cells in the light zone of the germinal center)..
CD44 It is used to detect the activation status of many immune cell subsets. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
CD8alpha  is expressed on the CD8 positive subset of T cells. It is also expressed on a macrophage subset. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
FoxP3  is expressed by T regulatory cells and T follicular regulatory cells. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
p53 is expressed in the nucleus of cells related to DNA remodeling. In the tonsil it can be found in the epithelia area and a few cells in the germinal center.
CD45 is expressed on all  hematopoietic cells. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP and can be used for downstream image analysis.

CD274 antibody detects the PD-1 protein (death receptor ligand) expressed on activated T cells, B cells, dendritic cells (DCs), antigen-presenting cells, keratiNcytes, monocytes, and various types of tumor cells. In the tonsil it is presend in the germinal center and in the epithelia cell area. It does Nt represent a priroritized target in tonsil OMAP.
Cytokeratin 7 is expressed by a subset of epithelia cells in the tonsil.
CD233 is a marker for erythrocytes. It detects regions in which erythrocyte products are enriched.
PCNA is a marker of proliferating cells. In the tonsil it can be found on epithelia cells and germinal center cells,.
CD163 is expressed on monocytes/macrophages. It is preferentally expressed on macrophages of the M2 type..
CD11b is expressed on monocytes/macrophages but also on subsets of other lymphocytes, like B1 B cells.
CD45RB is a splice variant of the CD45 gene. This splice variant is expressed on a B cell subset and NaiveT cells.
CD14 is a marker for blood derived macrophages and in the tonil it also stains the Folicular cell net work in the germinal center.
CD107a is expressed on a NK subset (CD57 negative) in the Germinal Center.
Cytokeratin 14 is expressed by epithelia cells in the tonsil

Ki67  is expressed in the nucleus of proliferating cells. It defines dark zone (Ki67++) of the germinal center. This marker is essential for assessing cell division and proliferation. This marker represents a core panel and prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
CD4 is expressed by subsets of T cells. This marker is also expressed on a subset of myeloid cells. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
CD31 stains endothelia cells in the tonsil. As there are no lymphatic vessels in the tonsil the endothelia cells stained are blood vessels.
CD45RA is a splice variant of the CD45 gene. This splice variant is expressed on NaiveCD4 and CD8 T cells and a B cell subset.
CD38 is a marker for activated B cells.
Cleaved PARP1 is expressed in aptoptotic cells. In the tonsil such cells can be found in the germinal centre (also cell fragments)
CD20 is expressed on  B cells and defines B cell follicles This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
Podoplanin stains lymphatic vessels (absent in tonsil) and is also expressed on Stroma and subset of Epithelia cells.
CD134 is an activation marker on T cells and marks newly activated T cells.
CD1c is expressed on mantle zone B cells and myeolid DC. This marker represents a core panel and prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.

Alpha smooth muscle actin defines the fibroblastic reticular network and vasculature of the tonsil. This is an essential marker for many cell types including smooth muscle cells and many subsets of fibroblasts. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
CD68 cannot be used to define a specific anatomical structure but is expressed by many subsets of myeloid cells. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.

CD79a is an antigen highly expressed by plasma cells.  In this panel, CD138 and the Plasma Cell marker are strongly expressed on plasma cells. Most plasma cells are located in the extra follicular region of the tonsil. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
CD45RO is  a splice variant of the CD45 gene. It is expressed on Memory T cells.
Vimentin defines stromal network of tonsil and serves as a pan-mesenchymal cell marker. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
CD11c is expressed on dendritic cells. It does Nt define a particular region in the tonsil. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
CD3 epsilon defines T cell zone and is an essential marker of T cells. This marker represents a core panel and prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
CD324 is expressed on epithelia cells.
HLA ABC is expressed on most cells and can be used as a segmentation marker
CD57 is expressed on a NK subset in the Germinal Center
Cytokeratin 5 is expressed by epithelia cells in the tonsil.

CD138 is a marker for plasma cells along with CD79a markers. Most plasma cells are located in the extra follicular region of the tonsil. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP. CD138 also defines the epithelium of the tonsil.
Cytokeratin 19 is expressed by epithelia cells in the tonsil.
Cytokeratin Class II is expressed by the extracellular matrix. In the tonsil it defines the  tonsillar crypt. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
HLA-DR is expressed on antigen presenting cells. It defines B cell follicles (HLA-DR+) and germinal centers (HLA-DR++).  This marker represents a core panel and prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
beta Actin is a universal cytoplasmic cell marker. In the tonsil it can be used to improve cell segmentation.
Cytokeratin HMW is expressed by epithelia cells in the tonsil.
Calponin is involved in cell mobility.
ESR1 is positive in many cells of the Tonsil. It can be used to improve cell segmentation in the Tonsil. Is is expressed in germinal center but not in the marginal zone.
ERB2 is expressed in many cell types also in the tonsil, for example in the epithelia cells. It can be used to improve cell segmentation.
